              "fill": "$--border",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 1
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Q79EO",
              "name": "bodyText",
              "fill": "#4B5563",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Our spaced repetition algorithm (SM-2) schedules words based on how well you know them. Words you get right are shown less frequently, while words you struggle with appear more often.\n\nEach correct answer increases the interval before the next review. Getting a word wrong resets it to a shorter interval so you can practice it more.\n\nYour proficiency is tracked per form — so even within the same word, different cases are scheduled independently.\n\nFor example, if you know the Accusative case of a word well but struggle with the Genitive, the Genitive form will appear more frequently in your practice sessions.\n\nThe algorithm considers:\n\n• Accuracy — how often you answer correctly\n• Response consistency — whether you've been improving\n• Time since last review — longer gaps increase priority\n\nOver time, well-known words naturally fade into longer review cycles, while challenging ones stay in active rotation until mastered.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "DM Sans",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
